Personas"},{"from":{"fname":"seed.Product Management.Target Customers","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":3,"offset":4},"end":{"line":3,"column":40,"offset":41},"indent":[]},"value":"seed.Product Management.Personas"}],"anchors":{"roman-pichler-persona-template":{"type":"header","text":"Roman Pichler Persona Template","value":"roman-pichler-persona-template","line":21,"column":0,"depth":1},"profiles":{"type":"header","text":"Profiles","value":"profiles","line":31,"column":0,"depth":2},"demographics":{"type":"header","text":"Demographics","value":"demographics","line":40,"column":0,"depth":1},"more-goals-needs-and-constraints-than-demographics":{"type":"header","text":"More Goals, Needs and Constraints than Demographics","value":"more-goals-needs-and-constraints-than-demographics","line":49,"column":0,"depth":1},"example-personas":{"type":"header","text":"Example Personas","value":"example-personas","line":54,"column":0,"depth":1},"everyone-is-not-a-persona":{"type":"header","text":"'EVERYONE' is not a persona","value":"everyone-is-not-a-persona","line":56,"column":0,"depth":2},"the-mom-persona":{"type":"header","text":"The 'mom' persona.","value":"the-mom-persona","line":62,"column":0,"depth":2},"23-sided-marketplaces-airbnb":{"type":"header","text":"2/3-sided marketplaces (AirBnb).","value":"23-sided-marketplaces-airbnb","line":63,"column":0,"depth":2},"airbnb-example":{"type":"header","text":"AirBnB example","value":"airbnb-example","line":64,"column":0,"depth":3},"doordash---3-sided-marketplace":{"type":"header","text":"DoorDash - 3 sided marketplace","value":"doordash---3-sided-marketplace","line":91,"column":0,"depth":3},"b2b":{"type":"header","text":"B2B","value":"b2b","line":95,"column":0,"depth":2},"mom":{"type":"header","text":"Mom","value":"mom","line":102,"column":0,"depth":2},"accountingbusiness":{"type":"header","text":"Accounting/Business","value":"accountingbusiness","line":107,"column":0,"depth":2},"multinational-tom":{"type":"header","text":"Multinational Tom","value":"multinational-tom","line":108,"column":0,"depth":3},"gill-small-business-owner":{"type":"header","text":"Gill Small Business Owner","value":"gill-small-business-owner","line":114,"column":0,"depth":3},"very-busy-persona":{"type":"header","text":"Very Busy Persona","value":"very-busy-persona","line":120,"column":0,"depth":2},"use-cases":{"type":"header","text":"Use Cases","value":"use-cases","line":126,"column":0,"depth":1},"multiple-personas":{"type":"header","text":"Multiple Personas","value":"multiple-personas","line":132,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"EVijZijYIRlEImKSUyKEl","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"personas\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#personas\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Personas</h1>\n<p>Customers are actual people who (could) use your product. </p>\n<p>Personas are customer types. Must represent real target market!! </p>\n<p><strong>Don't make personas for non-target markets! </strong></p>\n<p>Keep details sparse and focused on what is relevant to the product/use cases.</p>\n<p>Also, 'jobs to be done' based customer segmentation (Clayton Christensen). Great way to build good personas.</p>\n<h1 id=\"roman-pichler-persona-template\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#roman-pichler-persona-template\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Roman Pichler Persona Template</h1>\n<p><img src=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/assets/images/2022-03-17-16-58-07.png\" alt=\"From romanpichler.com\"></p>\n<p>When writing, write only stuff that's relevant to your product! Delete rest</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Priorities, related to your product/area of expertise</li>\n<li>Pain points</li>\n<li>Imagine customer journey, how do you beat the status quo? I.e., how do you do better than the curren tprocess</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"profiles\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#profiles\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Profiles</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Name </li>\n<li>Picture </li>\n<li>Details</li>\n<li>Goals </li>\n</ul>\n<p>format. Can do it in google docs/word, or use some specialized persona management tool</p>\n<h1 id=\"demographics\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#demographics\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Demographics</h1>\n<p>Overused, use demographic information only if relevant, else use goals/targets/objectives/constraints/feelings/etc.</p>\n<p>Focusing on common pain points/objectives/desires segment better than demographics!</p>\n<p>Try to make it a real persona.</p>\n<h1 id=\"more-goals-needs-and-constraints-than-demographics\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#more-goals-needs-and-constraints-than-demographics\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>More Goals, Needs and Constraints than Demographics</h1>\n<p>One way to look at it is 'what is this person trying to optimize for? What are their constraints '</p>\n<h1 id=\"example-personas\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#example-personas\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Example Personas</h1>\n<h2 id=\"everyone-is-not-a-persona\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#everyone-is-not-a-persona\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a><strong>'EVERYONE' is not a persona</strong></h2>\n<p>Way too broad, too vague, not actionable.</p>\n<h2 id=\"the-mom-persona\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#the-mom-persona\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>The 'mom' persona.</h2>\n<h2 id=\"23-sided-marketplaces-airbnb\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#23-sided-marketplaces-airbnb\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>2/3-sided marketplaces (AirBnb).</h2>\n<h3 id=\"airbnb-example\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#airbnb-example\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>AirBnB example</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Renter\n'Feel like a local' culture.\n'Cost'.\n'Doesn't care about service.'</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Host </p>\n<p>Figure out motivation for renting the place. </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Sharing couch/room.</p>\n<p>Maximize revenue.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Retired couple, renting out vacation home.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Prefer longer stays and people who would treat place as their own.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Persona Business Traveller (<strong>non-target</strong>)</p>\n<ol>\n<li>There to work, not 'feel like a local'.</li>\n<li>Favor service and convenience over saving costs, connecting with host, etc.</li>\n<li>Costs are discounted by various discounts, aimed at corporate customers.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>So the business travelers will not be the best customers for AirBnb.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"doordash---3-sided-marketplace\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#doordash---3-sided-marketplace\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>DoorDash - 3 sided marketplace</h3>\n<p>See <a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/CrAWkVsx2tCnJARRILuG4#^usergoals\">Doordash Talk</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"b2b\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#b2b\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>B2B</h2>\n<p>The buyer and customer are different personas. E.g.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>CEO vs HR/Ops persona.</li>\n<li>Parent vs Child Persona</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"mom\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#mom\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Mom</h2>\n<p>Can my mom use it? Middle aged person, who's not a technology early adopter.</p>\n<h2 id=\"accountingbusiness\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#accountingbusiness\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Accounting/Business</h2>\n<h3 id=\"multinational-tom\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#multinational-tom\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Multinational Tom</h3>\n<p> Simple accounting/office/shift management software might not have all features\nTom needs, e.g. management of different offices, tax systems, etc.</p>\n<p> Can tolerate bad UI, as staff's job is more specialized and they can learn it.</p>\n<h3 id=\"gill-small-business-owner\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#gill-small-business-owner\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Gill Small Business Owner</h3>\n<p>Doesnt' need all features Tom might need <strong>AND</strong> doesn't want to be especially trained to use a software that supports them all.</p>\n<p>Can't tolerate bad UI as she needs to run the whole business..</p>\n<h2 id=\"very-busy-persona\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#very-busy-persona\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Very Busy Persona</h2>\n<p>If the persona you're targeting is very busy, beside solving the pain point, usage  should require <strong>no training</strong>.</p>\n<h1 id=\"use-cases\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#use-cases\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Use Cases</h1>\n<p>How would a a given persona use the product to solve a specific problem?    </p>\n<h2 id=\"multiple-personas\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#multiple-personas\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Multiple Personas</h2>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/CrAWkVsx2tCnJARRILuG4\">Doordash Talk</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/c7rsts0s84pjnj28m21ee3s\">Product School Book</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/nebipgh2jbwp0qaatg3e4us\">Strategic Understanding of The Company</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/1uzfbgjhsij4hmtrkrkxq8p\">Target Customers</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"wn8PE1RhG0znK1alrGFYv","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1647507231129,"created":1631901573363,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"db285659ccac8b133c384de1ef51de66","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-stefans-notes":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to Stefan's Notes!","value":"welcome-to-stefans-notes","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":["mxzxxu8z4e6krz99ht96y9d","W1EOZ27Tqx6RbiA2aW3DI","DyoLE2kwm9rRfRZhBGxPW","idhfogizmtcmvaamtalp3o3","4w8wBCSRvYUnGIZeozW03","vB321AipYCs6ldVC0APs9","h6WVdl1UTWVXeWuMJSZ1f","bth6m0exy9q9loxib1mc4al","4abAmH56ausbldEJbZokx","JyOFJ5NTPSVWMfiDy951X","0OO7fjCpcaGZg5qDRZr8z","138666663","pohXgII67dAxnoufG7yAP","42r6290iqzLPmg9BY7fIp","3hoLerNJHjNkDziIKlFF2","T6meT3UNw0nRorEbzoPSl","hIOTXIIBj3vmhG1xc91lA","tnFlQuOAGPkbU2fZI7Cb1","Jb3w3f4x8kixLhrjUW6S1","LV6q5jlD2xtCF6yYFEqFC","ENDcCZFjAW9h66eDoFg7I","b5IeREnsTbeggC7rmWV0p","nbBlQzRv6upNd7EAsifqo","xcJ4vbwPtrOHtYsSgUaQi","D41QyIueG2TcjTWPyDwAs","3Gihb6jm1N7h9TvHP0b3m","d9qyiiGgDJAIdYBgV8NHB","OA3izVK70lO3wm3AQ9ac0","srwEq3ZSQj5S0POsjEszf","h1ME0EUHZQrdOQWdI83oP"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"# Welcome to Stefan's Notes!\n\n        \n